    created_at: "2026-04-02T06:00:00Z",
    body: "<p style='color:#6a4b8f;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:18px'>By Khyati Srivastava</p><p>A red umbrella, snug and dry,<br>had only ever known the sky<br>when storms rolled in and rain came down,<br>it never saw the sunny town.</p><p>It sighed inside the closet dark,<br>I wish that I could see the park,<br>the buttercups, the open air,<br>but rain is all I get to share.</p><p>Then little Maya had a thought,<br>on the hottest day the summer brought,<br>she took the red umbrella out,<br>and twirled it as she ran about.</p><p>Not for the rain, but for the shade,<br>a cool round shelter that it made,<br>the picnic blanket, friends, and pie,<br>all sheltered from the blazing sky.</p><p>The red umbrella beamed with pride,<br>so glad it had not stayed inside,<br>for sunny days, it learned at last,<br>can need you just as storms once asked.</p>",
